Third Phase
49 Juventude - Fluminense                   1-1  (27/03)    1-2  (03/04)
50 Confiança - Brasiliense                  0-0  (13/03)    1-4  (03/04)
51 Bahia - Portuguesa                       3-0  (27/03)    2-2  (03/04)
52 Atlético-MG - Internacional              2-0  (28/03)    2-3  (03/04)
53 Figueirense - São Paulo                  3-1  (28/03)    1-6  (03/04)
54 CSA - Vasco                              2-1  (27/03)    0-4  (03/04) [*]
55 Botafogo - Paraná                        1-3  (28/03)    1-1  (03/04)
56 Corinthians - Cruzeiro                   2-2  (13/03)    3-2  (03/04)

[*] In the first leg against CSA, Vasco da Gama fielded defender João Carlos
who would be suspended due to his third yellow card received in the second
leg against Santa Cruz. That suspension, however, did not happen. Later on,
after losing the second leg, CSA required a suitable punishment for Vasco
da Gama, with loss of five points and its consequent elimination of the Cup.
But the STJD (supreme sports justice tribunal) decided to penalise Vasco
da Gama with fine of R$ 2.000,00 instead of the loss of points, confirming
his classification. 
Quarterfinals
